22/09/2005
TIRANA, Albania -- President Alfred Moisiu attended the maritime exercise "Co-operative Engagement 2005" on Wednesday (21 September), in the Vlora Bay.
A total of 11 NATO and Partnership for Peace countries are participating.
Moisiu stressed the importance of the exercise, in view of Albania's NATO membership aspirations.
Also Wednesday, Moisiu met with US Ambassador to Tirana Marcie Ries.
He briefed her on his recent trip to New York, and on the bilateral meetings he held on the sidelines of the UN summit.
They also discussed recent political developments in Albania, particularly an effort by the new government to return the National Informative Service to the control of the interior ministry.
(Albanian News - 22/09/05;
Albanian President's Web site - 21/09/05)
